node.text:
The Veluwemeer Aqueduct is a waterway that measures 25 meters long and 19 meters wide.
Located in Harderwijk, Eastern #Netherlands, this superb footage shows us the aqueduct's unique design from high above.

Video via @fatstudios 🚢

Same shot, cropped twice 🤯
Video & photo by @trystane of Mount Rainier, Washington. 🇺🇸

Rainier is one of the Washington’s most iconic landmarks. Board the Mount Rainier Scenic Railroad, hike among the wildflowers amidst its nature trails, or even go skiing, snowboarding, and snowshoeing during the winter. No trip to the state is complete without a visit here! 🏔

Explore. Share. Inspire: #earthfocus

node.text:
A dust devil spotted by @rodrigoviverosphoto in Alto Las Vizcachas, Chile. 🇨🇱 Have you ever seen one in person? 🌪

Dust devils, or sand devils, are an interesting phenomena. They form in an upward motion from the ground to the sky. They are short-lived whirlwinds that are mainly harmless.

Dust devils form when hot air at the surface begins to rise rapidly with much cooler air above it. The hot air then stretches and causes a spinning motion, much like a tornado. They are short-lived because cold air eventually gets pulled in and dissipates the dust devil.

🎥 @rodrigoviverosphoto
📍 Alto Las Vizcachas, Chile

Explore. Share. Inspire: #earthfocus
